                <note rend="inline" type="source">195.91/9–1549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Macdonald</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-15T15:00:00+09:00"
                            >September 15, 1949—3 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 15—3:52 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>479. Called on Governor early this morning re Deptel 308, September 13, also
                    handed him <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>. He said matter not under his
                    judisdiction but will communicate with Ministry National Defense and Foreign
                    Office. Endeavoring obtain appointment with special commissioner Ministry
                    Foreign Affairs to discuss this matter so he will not feel I have gone over his
                    head to Governor causing him loss of face. I plan tell him question referred to
                    Governor in his capacity chairman Southeast Military and Political
                    Headquarters.</p>
                <p>Seeing K.C. Wu late this afternoon regarding same.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Macdonald</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
